Ned Nwoko, the billionaire husband of actress Regina Daniels, has reacted to claims of taking another wife. Nwoko, in an Instagram post, denied allegations of having secretly taken another wife according to several online reports. The politician, who termed the news as ‘fake’, explained if he desired to take another wife, it would never be done in secrecy. “NED NWOKO MARRIES ANOTHER WIFE…This is fake news and YOU shouldn’t help to propagate it. “If I want to marry, it will not be done in secrecy. There is a particular group of little-minded faceless individuals who believe they can gain followership in social media by using my name to create sensational news every week.   Nkechi Blessing overjoyed as Davido hugs, pecks actress     Killing in the name of Biafra     EU announces three areas for Africa’s support after…   - Advertisement - “I will keep being law-abiding and reporting the miscreants to the police for appropriate actions. “When such misguided individuals are arrested, don’t accuse me of using the law against them.,” he tweeted. Nwoko’s post came days after a popular blogger alleged he had taken a new wife. The blogger also noted the former House of Representatives member was accompanied by his new wife to a recent political rally in Asaba, Delta State. SPONSORED